<title>Nemzet 1996.08.06</title><BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000"><h1>Nemzet 1996.08.06</h1><!-- body="start" --><pre>N     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE  TTTTTTTNN    N  E        MM   MM       Z   E           TN N   N  E        M M M M      Z    E           TN  N  N  EEEE     M  M  M     Z     EEEE        TN   N N  E        M     M    Z      E           TN    NN  E        M     M   Z       E           TN     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE     T--->> M A G Y A R   I N T E R N E T   V I L A G L A P <<---</pre><h3>==<br><br>HAZAI SAJTO  <br><br>Sajtokivonatok napi- es hetilapokbol [Szent Hirek, a Sorok Kozt    <br>Olvaso szabad velemenyeivel tarkitva] UM: Uj M.o., MN:    <br>MagyarNemzet, NSZ:  Nepszabadsag, MH: Magyar Hirlap, NSZV:    <br>Nepszava, EH: Esti Hirlap,  HVG: Heti Vilaggazdasag, VG:    <br>Vilaggazdasag, NG: NapiGazdasag. A magyar copyright egyszer mar    <br>megjelent napi- es hetilap anyagot szabadon utankozolhetonek tart.<br><br>1. Kulfold<br><br>[Vege az olimpianak]<br><br>Atlantaban a zarounnepseggel befejezodtek a XXVI. Nyari Olimpiai <br>Jatekok. A lapok beszamoloi szerint az amerikaiaknak mindenkeppen <br>csalodast okozott, amikor Juan Antonio Samaranch, a NOB elnoke csak <br>"rendkivuli esemenynek" nevezte a jatekokat, nem pedig minden <br>idok legnagyobb olimpiai rendezvenyenek. A magyar lapok <br>hangsulyozzak: sportoloink elmaradtak ugyan a szouli es a bercelonai <br>olimpian nyujtott teljesitmenyuktol, szegyenkezesre azonban semmi <br>ok. Az osszesitett eremtablazaton elert 12. helyezes azt bizonyitja: a <br>magyar sport meg mindig vilagszinvonalu. [Jo mi? "MEG MINDIG" - <br>vagyis mar igen hamar elkovetkezik a teljes letores]  Am Gallov <br>Rezso allamtitkar, az OTSH elnoke figyelmeztet: a jovobeni hasonlo <br>sikerekhez a korabbi anyagi tamogatas aligha lesz elegendo. Gallov <br>nem titkolta, hogy sportoloink nemileg elmaradtak a varakozasoktol. <br>Schmitt Pal, a MOB elnoke, a NOB alelnoke viszont elegedett a <br>szereplessel (NSZ, NSZV, MH).<br><br>[Borsos NATO-belepodij]<br><br>Amerikai kutatok szerint 10-15 ev alatt 17 milliard dollarba fog <br>kerulni, hogy a negy visegradi orszag kialakitsa a NATO-nak is <br>megfelelo onvedelmi rendszeret. A HM NATO foosztalyanak vezetoje, <br>Martinusz Zoltan szerint a szamitasnak van realitasa, bar az egyelore <br>csak feltetelezeseken alapul (MH). [Mig kapna M.o. egy "masodik <br>adossag" felveteleert? Fuggetlensege ELVESZTESET, es Trianon <br>HARMADIK BEBETONOZASAT. Kerdes, hogy ha 17 milliard dollart <br>FIZETNENEK ezert nekunk, nem kellene akkor is kirohogni ezeket!]<br><br>[Borisz car mar csak jelkep - duhong az oroklesi csata a harckepes <br>politikusok kozott]<br><br>Borisz Jelcin orosz elnok meghosszabbitja szabadsagat, csak <br>kozvetlenul a beiktatas elott ter vissza Moszkvaba a barhivai <br>szanatoriumbol - jelentettek be tegnap Moszkvaban (MH).<br><br>[Tores Clinton es Nyugateuropa politikaja kozott]<br><br>Teheran es Tripoli tiltakozasa ellenere Bill Clinton elnok tegnap <br>alairta az ugynevezett D'Amato-torvenyt, amely sulyos kereskedelmi <br>szankciokat helyez kilatasba azoknak a kulfoldi vallalatoknak, <br>amelyek 40 millio dollar felett szandekoznak befektetni koolaj- es <br>foldgazerdekeltsegekbe Iranban es Libiaban (MN). [Francia es angol <br>kulugyminiszterek maris kijelentettek, nem elfogadhato ha az USA <br>akar szabalyokat bevezetni a vilag orszagai szamara]<br><br>[Gruziai maffiavezerek oldoklesebe bonyolodtunk - bravo]<br><br>Az osztrak hatosagok attol felnek, hogy a Sanikidze-gyilkossaggal <br>kapcsolatban Budapesten fogva tartott ket gyanusitott ugyeben <br>Gruzia esetleg nyomast gyakorolhat a magyar hatosagokra, hogy azok <br>tagadjak meg az orizetesek kiadatasat Ausztrianak - irta het vegi <br>szamaban a becsi Kurier. Tovabbi osztrak aggodalom, hogy az <br>orizeteseket eppen magyarorszagi fogva tartasuk alatt erheti esetleg <br>valami. Szerintuk ugyanis valamelyik erintett keleti <br>maffiacsoportosulasnak konnyuszerrel sikerulhet a magyar <br>bortonben az ottani rabok kozott is bergyilkost talalnia. A merenylet <br>julius 11-en este tortent Becsben: az aldozat egy 50 eves gruz <br>uzletember - allitolagos maffiavezer -, akit az 1995. augusztus 29-i, <br>Eduard Sevardnadze gruz elnok elleni merenylettel gyanusitanak.<br><br>[A katolikus egyhaz "vilagrend"-fele, az orosz orthodox egyhaz <br>"nemzeti erok fele" tart.]<br><br>Az orosz ortodox egyhaz Szent Szinodusa mondott nemet II. Alekszij <br>patriarka es II. Janos Pal papa tervezett magyarorszagi talalkozojara. <br>A ki nem mondott okok kozott elsosorban az szerepel, hogy az orosz <br>ortodox egyhazban egyre erosebb az allammal valo azonosulas <br>torekvese, s ez a regi nacionalizmus szemben all katolikus egyhaz <br>univerzalis jellegevel - irta vasarnapi szamaban a La Stampa cimu <br>olasz ujsag. A lap emlekeztet arra, hogy minden keszen allt a <br>Pannonhalman tervezett talalkozora, annak letrejottet mind II. Janos <br>Pal, mind II. Alekszij szerette volna.<br><br> 2. Hatarontul<br><br>[Erdely - Nagyvaradi Magyar Reformatus Vilagtalalkozo]<br><br>A nagyvaradi unnepelyes megnyito utan Bihar, illetve Szatmar <br>megyeben folytatodott a harmadik magyar reformatus vilagtalalkozo <br>rendezvenysorozata. Bar a roman tomegtajekoztatasi eszkozok <br>kenytelenek beismerni, hogy a vilagtalalkozo rendben zajlik, <br>igyekeznek kivetnivalot talalni a rendezvenyben. A kozszolgalati <br>televizio es a roman radio hiradasaiban arrol tajekoztatott, hogy <br>Lorantffy Zsuzsanna szobrat a nemzeti kolto, Eminescu horthystak <br>altal ledontott szobranak helyen allitottak fel. Arrol is beszamoltak, <br>hogy a szoborallitashoz nem volt meg minden engedely, s igy a <br>nagyvaradi polgarmester egymillio 600 ezer lejre, mintegy 80 ezer <br>forintra birsagolta meg a szervezoket (MH). A hitbeli testverekkel <br>valo talalkozas orome es a magyar anyanyelvvel szorosan <br>osszekapcsolodo reformatus onazonossagtudat meltosaggal valo <br>vallalasa jellemezte a Magyar Reformatusok III. Vilagtalalkozojanak <br>szombati es vasarnapi fo rendezvenyeit az erdelyi varosokban. Az <br>unnepi alkalmak szonokai ismetelten koszonetet mondtak a roman <br>hatosagoknak es a varosi onkormanyzatok vezetoinek, hogy az <br>erkezo kulfoldi vendegek hataron valo beleptetese elozekenyen, <br>gyorsan es zokkenomentesen tortent, es lehetove tettek a <br>vilagtalalkozo korlatozasok nelkuli megrendezeset. A Magyar <br>Reformatusok III. Vilagtalalkozoja tajegysegi rendezvenyeinek <br>kereteben vasarnap a Nagyvarad melletti Hegykozpalyiban es <br>Hegykozujlakon Hegykozi Napokat tartottak. Hegykozujlakon a <br>hegykozi Nepfoiskola epuletenek unnepelyes atadasan Csurka Istvan <br>mondott unnepi beszedet. A Rompres allami es a Mediafax <br>maganhirugynokseg, valamint a bukaresti radio vasarnap rovid <br>tudositasokban adott hirt a magyar reformatus vilagtalalkozo <br>nagyvaradi nyitanyarol. Tokes Laszlo, a Magyar Reformatus <br>Vilagszovetseg uj elnoke altal ismertetett nyilatkozatbol a Rompres <br>azt a mondatot idezte, amely a roman jogallamisag feltetlen <br>elismeresekent emliti azt, hogy ezt azt orszagot valasztottak a <br>talalkozo szinhelyeul. A Mediafax hirugynokseg kiemelte, hogy Tokes <br>Laszlo puspok koszonetet mondott Nagyvarad vezetesenek azert, <br>hogy sok viszontagsag utan vegul is lehetove tette a rendezveny <br>lebonyolitasat az eredetileg tervezett szinhelyen. A vilagtalalkozo <br>megnyitojarol beszamolt az AP amerikai es az AFP francia <br>hirugynokseg is. Az AP tudositasaban megemliti, hogy a roman <br>hatosagok nem probaltak megakadalyozni a rendezvenyt, bar <br>korabban figyelmeztettek, hogy az esetleges politikai es teruleti <br>kovetelesek felmerulese feszultseget okozhat. Az AFP is kiter arra, <br>hogy a roman hatosagok ova intettek attol, nehogy irredenta <br>jelentestartalmat kapjanak az esemenyen elhangzottak.<br><br>[Felvidek - totok a magyar autonomia ellen]<br><br>Szlovakia elvben nem ert egyet Magyarorszag ama kulpolitikai <br>logikajaval, amely szerint Budapestnek megkulonboztetett <br>figyelemben kellene reszesitenie a hataron tuli magyar <br>kisebbsegeket. A szlovak kulugyi tarca ugy veli, az autonomia nem <br>alapveto feltetel a magyar kisebbsegek identitasanak megorzesehez. <br>Mindezt Jozef Sestak szlovak kulugyi allamtitkar mondta el Benyo <br>Palnak, a pozsonyi magyar nagykovetseg ugyvivojenek tegnapi <br>talalkozasuk alkalmabol. A jugoszlav kormany kozlemenyben fejezte <br>ki aggodalmat a "magyar-magyar csucstalalkozon" elfogadott <br>nyilatkozattal kapcsolatban (MH).<br><br>[Totok boldogok Clinton autonomiaellenes politikaja lattan]<br><br>A szlovak kulugyi tarca szombaton hosszu nyilatkozatban udvozolte, <br>hogy Christopher Smith, az amerikai kongresszus Helsinki-<br>bizottsaganak tarselnoke biralo velemenyt tett kozze a magyar-<br>magyar csucs resztvevoinek az autonomia kerdeseben kialakitott <br>allaspontjarol. A pozsonyi nyilatkozat "nagyra ertekeli Chistopher <br>Smith objektiv allaspontjat" - aki allitolag csalodottan ertesult arrol, <br>hogy a budapesti magyar-magyar csucs resztvevoi nem a konkret <br>problemakkal, hanem az autonomia es az onkormanyzat ketertelmu <br>tamogatasaval foglalkoztak. A szlovak nyilatkozat szerint Smith <br>megjegyezte: a szoban forgo fogalmak tisztazatlansaga olyan <br>benyomast kelthet, hogy a magyar-magyar csucs kozos <br>nyilatkozataban jelen van az a "nehezen leplezheto szandek" hogy <br>"Budapest a jelenlegi hatarokon tulra probalja kiterjeszteni <br>befolyasat, vagy vissza akarja hozni azokat az idoket, amikor minden <br>magyar egy allamban egyesulve" elt.<br><br>[Felvidek - millecentenarium emlekmu elleni vandal tamadas]<br><br>Vasarnapra virradora harom ismeretlen tettes meggyalazta a <br>juniusban felallitott csicsoi millecentenariumi emlekmuvet - irta a <br>hetfoi Uj Szo. A vandalok harom granittombot letortek az <br>emlekmutarto oszlopbol, kalapaccsal es vesovel karositottak meg az <br>emlektablat. A tettesek az alapzatnak is nekiestek, de egy helybeli <br>lako megjelenese megzavarta oket. A komaromi jarasbeli kozseg <br>emlekmuvet a helyi onkormanyzat tamogatasaval epitette a <br>Csemadok helyi szervezete (MN).<br><br>[Karpatalja - millecentenariumi emlekmu tervei]<br><br>Millecentenariumi emlekmu felallitasat kezdemenyezi Beregszaszon a <br>Beregvideki Magyar Kulturalis Szovetseg. A magyar tobbsegu <br>karpataljai varos kepviselotestulete az elkepzelest felkarolva <br>legutobbi ulesen ugy dontott, hogy a honfoglalasi emlekmu helyeul a <br>sportcsarnok elotti parkot jeloli ki - adta hirul a vereckei emlekmu <br>es megemlekezes kijevi lefujasanak bejelentesevel csaknem <br>egyidejuleg az ungvari Karpati Igaz Szo hetvegi szama.<br><br>[Szlovak kulturalis kozpont nyilt Eszak-Magyarorszagon]<br><br>A CTK pragai hirugynokseg rovid tenyhirben szamolt be arrol, hogy <br>szombaton az eszak-magyarorszagi Bankon felavattak a Ludovit <br>Sturrol elnevezett szlovak kulturalis kozpontot. A tudosito kiemeli, <br>hogy Eva Mitrova, a Szlovak Koztarsasag budapesti nagykovete <br>rendkivul fontos esemenynek nevezte a kozpont megnyitasat. <br><br>3. Gazdasag<br><br>[Adopres]<br><br>A Penzugyminiszterium tegnap kuldte meg az adotorvenyek <br>javaslatait a kormanynak. Ez a valtozat mar tartalmazza a jovo evre <br>javasolt adotablat is. A legmagasabb adokulcs 44 szazalek lenne, <br>amelyet evi masfel millio forint utan kellene fizetni. A <br>legalacsonyabb kulcsra 20 szazalekot javasolnak. A tervek szerint <br>megszunne a kettos adotabla, ez azonban nem jelentene az <br>adojovairas megszuneset. A munkaviszonybol szarmazo jovedelmek <br>utan 18 szazalekos ilyen jovairasu adokedvezmenyt lehetne igenybe <br>venni, ez azonban nem lehetne tobb, mint 37 ezer forint. A <br>szamitasok szerint a javasolt adotabla 1,5 szazalekkal csokkentene az <br>atlagos adoterhelest, 22,5 szazalekrol hozzavetolegesen 21 szazalekra. <br>Az adosavokat jelentosen szethuzna a tervezet es csokkennenek az <br>adokulcsok is. Iden 380 ezer forintos eves jovedelem utan mar 40 <br>szazalek az adokulcs, jovore varhatoan 600 ezer forintra emelkedne a <br>savhatar.(NSZ)<br><br>[Mar az adoztatason is hajbakap az SZDSZ es MSZP]<br><br>Szekeres Imre, az MSZP frakciovezetoje szerint a jovo evi szemelyi <br>jovedelemadozasban a felso, 48 szazalekos kulcs csokkentese helyett <br>az adosavokat kellene valorizalni, azaz a savhatarokat emelni. Gaal <br>Gyula, az SZDSZ frakciovezeto-helyettese viszont ugy latja: ez az <br>elgondolas ellentmond a ket kormanypart kozti korabbi <br>megallapodasnak (MH).<br><br>[Megugrott a munkanelkuliseg]<br><br>Julius vegen 494500 munkanelkulit tartottak nyilvan <br>Magyarorszagon, 12500-zal tobbet, mint junius vegen. A <br>munkanelkulisegi rata juliusban elerte a 10,8 szazalekot. A <br>regisztralt munkanelkuliek szamanak emelkedese a palyakezdo <br>fiatalok nagyobb aranyu jelentkezesevel magyarazhato. A <br>nyilvantartott palyakezdo munkanelkuliek szama juliusban 33600-<br>rol 47500-ra emelkedett (NSZV, MH).<br><br>[Kisibolasra keszen all 231 milliard forint]<br><br>A lakossag brutto megtakaritasa az ev elso feleben az MNB elozetes <br>adatai szerint 231 milliard forinttal, 11 szazalekkal nott, s a <br>megtakaritott osszeg a fel ev vegen meghaladta a 2339 milliard <br>forintot - tajekoztatta a KSH az MTI-t. Az adatokbol kitunik, hogy a <br>betetkonyvekben, ertekpapirokban elhelyezett penz az egy evvel <br>ezelottihez kepest folyo aron 24,5 szazalekkal, volumeneben mintegy <br>egy szazalekkal emelkedett. A lakossagi megtakaritasokon belul a <br>forintmegtakaritas az elso hat honap alatt 217 milliard forinttal <br>novekedett, ez a novekmeny tobb mint ketszerese annak, mint <br>amennyi a mult ev azonos idoszakaban volt. Osszessegeben a <br>forintmegtakaritas-allomany a felev vegen megkozelitette az 1887 <br>milliard forintot. A takarekbetet-allomany 85 milliard forinttal nott <br>az ev elso feleben, ami tobb mint hetszerese a tavalyi ev azonos <br>idoszakaban elert novekedesnek. A lakossagi hitelallomany az elozo <br>ev azonos idoszakahoz viszonyitva 8,3 milliard forinttal csokkent, <br>junius vegere 288 milliard forintra merseklodott (MN). [A <br>bizonytalanul jo - illetve a biztosan rossz- kilatasok miatt egyre <br>inkabb "likvid" allapotban (penzben, ertekpapirokban) tartja <br>vagyonat a kleptokratak ujgazdag retege. Minthogy a forint immar <br>korlatlanul atvalthato, ez a 231 milliard forint lesz az elsok kozott, <br>amely eltunik majd mint szurke szamar a kodben]<br><br>[A recesszio elerte a MNB kamatlabakat is (ld. recessziot deklaralo <br>hirt alabb)]<br><br>Tegnap az MNB 0,25 szazalekponttal csokkentette repokamatait. Ez <br>meglepte a piaci szereplok tobbseget, mivel a legutobbi <br>kamatmersekles ota csak harom het telt el, annak hatasa eppen csak <br>beepult az arakba. A mostani kamatlefaragas eredmenyekent tovabb <br>csokkenhetnek az allampapirhozamok - ami az allamhaztartas <br>hianyanak finanszirozasa szempontjabol pozitiv -, de a banki beteti <br>kamatok is - ami viszont a lakossag szempontjabol nem annyira <br>kedvezo (VG).<br><br> 4. Belfold<br><br>[Nincs penz 4,5%-os beremelesre sem]<br><br>A kormany a kozponti koltsegvetesbol vagy a Munkaero-piaci Alap <br>tobbletebol "kolcsonzott" penzbol egesziti ki a koltsegvetesi szfera <br>idei beremeleset, mivel szinte bizonyosra veheto, hogy az <br>onkormanyzatok nem tudjak kifizetni az idei bermegallapodasban <br>vallalt 4,5 szazalekos emelest. Ez csaknem 13,5 milliard forintot <br>jelent. (NSZ)<br><br>[Onkormanyzatok csodben]<br><br>Kara Pal onkormanyzati helyettes allamtitkar elmondta: a BM adatai <br>szerint az iden eddig mindossze egyetlen telepules jelentett csodot, <br>szemben a tavalyi ottel. Kara ennel sokkal nagyobb gondnak tartja, <br>hogy onkormanyzatok sora keptelen befejezni a korabban <br>megkezdett beruhazasokat, bar konkret szamokrol meg nem tudott <br>nyilatkozni. Ugyanakkor szukseg lenne arra, hogy az egyes kotelezo <br>onkormanyzati feladatok minimumanak ellatasahoz szukseges penzt <br>a koltsegvetes maradektalanul biztositsa. A helyettes allamtitkar <br>arrol is beszamolt, hogy a kozelmultban Zala megyeben <br>megvizsgaltak, mely telepulesek valhatnak fizeteskeptelenne. A <br>tipikusan aprofalvas terseg 250-nel tobb onkormanyzatara kiterjedo <br>tapasztalata szerint ket helyen csaknem bizonyosan adossagrendezesi <br>eljarast kell kezdemenyezni, de nem kizart, hogy meg ket tovabbi <br>telepules is csodbe juthat. Zalaban tehat minden szazadik <br>onkormanyzatnak szembe kell neznie a fizeteskeptelenseg <br>veszelyevel. Szerinte felelosseggel senki sem nyilatkozhat arrol, hogy <br>a kozeljovoben hany telepules jelent csodot. Az teny, hogy nehany <br>kozseg nem fizet mar villanyszamlat, s van olyan telepules, ahol a <br>pedagogusok nem kaptak meg idoben a fizetesuket.(MH) Az Allami <br>Privatizacios es Vagyonkezelo Rt. az Alkotmanybirosag dontesere <br>var, ezert keslekedik az onkormanyzatok gazkozmureszvenyeinek <br>atadasaval. A legfobb biroi testulet mondja ki, hogy a belterulet hany <br>szazaleka illeti meg a telepuleseket. Az onkormanyzatok 90 <br>szazalekot varnak. A MN hirul adja, hogy a belteruleti fold jogan az <br>onkormanyzatoknak az APV Rt. az iden 15,5 milliard forintot  adott <br>at keszpenzben, 4,5 milliardot reszveny es 41,9 milliard forint erteku <br>vagyont pedig uzletresz formajaban. Ezenkivul meg 7,8 milliard <br>forint keszpenzre es csaknem 20 milliard forint erteku reszvenyre <br>szamithatnak a teruleti onkormanyzatok. Az allami vagyonbol a <br>legtobb a fovarosi onkormanyzatoknak jutott: eddig keszpenzben <br>tobb mint 3,8 milliard forintot kaptak, es meg 15,3 milliard forint <br>erteku reszvenyre tarthatnak igenyt. (MH)<br><br>[Meg egyet tekernek az adopresen]<br><br>Az egeszsegugyi jarulek jovore maximum ket szazalekponttal <br>csokkentheto. A jarulekkoteles jovedelmek kore a honorariumokkal <br>es a tiszteletdijakkal bovulhet. A tervek szerint jovore minden szja-<br>koteles bevetel utan jarulekot kellene fizetni. A vallalkozok altal <br>fizetendo egeszsegbiztositasi jarulek minimalis havi osszege 3100-<br>3200 forint lesz, ezert azonban nem jar tappenz vagy egyeb penzbeni <br>juttatas. Minderrol Simsa Peter, az Egeszsegbiztositasi  Onkormanyzat <br>alelnoke beszelt ujsagirok elott hetfon (MN).<br><br>[Tandij felso hatara a csillagos eg?]<br><br>Az 1997-98-as tanevtol esedekes tandij felso hataranak <br>megallapitasa kapcsan a muvelodesi tarca es a hallgatok <br>kepviseloinek allaspontja nemileg kozeledett a tegnapi targyalason, <br>am megallapodas meg nincs. Megegyeztek viszont a felek abban, <br>hogy az elvi egyeztetesek utan a muvelodesi miniszterium elkesziti a <br>tandijrendelet szoveget (MH).<br><br>[Uj berendezkedes a mediaban]<br><br>Hajdu Istvan, a Magyar Radio Reszvenytarsasag elnoke augusztus <br>elsejei hatallyal kinevezte Juhasz Juditot es Zavecz Ferencet <br>alelnoknek. Hajdu kozolte: szakmailag ket alkalmas szemelyt <br>valaszott a posztra. Zavecz Ferenc, aki eddig is az MR alelnokekent <br>tevekenykedett, tovabbra is a gazdasagi terulet feladatait latja el. <br>Juhasz Judit - aki ezt megelozoen a Westel Radiotelefon Kft. PR-<br>igazgatoja volt - a musorkeszitessel es a tarsadalmi kapcsolatokkal <br>foglalkozik (MH). Kozos sajtotajekoztaton tiltakoztak a <br>mediakuratoriumok vezetoi a finanszirozas befolyasolasat celzo <br>kormanyzati szandek ellen. Az MR, az MTV es a Duna TV <br>kozalapitvanyait kezelo testuletek a media fuggetlenseget feltik a <br>kormany julius 24-ei hatarozatatol, amely a kabinet fennhatosaga ala <br>vonna a mediatestuletek gazdalkodasat, az elofizetesi dij beszedeset <br>es megszuntetne a sugarzasi dij atvallalasat. (A sugarzasi dij <br>atvallalasaval, a musorszolgaltatasi koltsegeknek megfelelo <br>koltsegvetesi tamogatasi kotelezettseg vallalasaval a politika a <br>kozszolgalatisag tamogatasat vallalta.) A kuratoriumi elnoksegek altal <br>"ujraallamositasnak" erzett torekvesek Gyorgy Gabor, a radio <br>kuratoriumanak elnoke szerint egy folyamat elso allomasat <br>jelenthetik. Ez a folyamat a fuggetlen media kormanybefolyas ala <br>rendelesehez vezethet. Az elnokok hangsulyoztak: a kormany <br>torekveseinek nem politikai, hanem penzugyi motivumai vannak. <br>Nem az ideologia, hanem a koltsegvetes erdekei diktaltak a <br>kormanyhatarozatot a media ertekszempontjainak teljes figyelmen <br>kivul hagyasaval (NSZV).<br><br>[Egy dologban maris utolertuk a hires Nyugatot. Na, mi az?]<br><br>Szakertok szerint napjainkban az orszag es kulonosen a fovaros <br>kabitoszerrel valo fertozottsege elerte a Nyugat-Europaban mar <br>evtizedek ota allandosult szintet. Ez az allapot csaknem harom <br>evtized alatt alakult ki, am az ennek megfelelo bunuldozes a <br>rendorseg strukturaja meg ma is elegtelennek tunik a helyzet <br>kezelesehez - allitjak a kabitoszerellenes ugyek specialistai. <br>Napjainkban mar szinte minden akadaly nelkul hozza lehet jutni <br>barmilyen narkotikumhoz. Rendorsegi szakertok szerint Budapest, <br>Miskolc, Pecs, Szeged es az uduloovezetek szamos ifjusagi <br>szorakozohelyen es az utcakon is nyiltan arusitjak a legkulonfelebb <br>drogokat. Szakertok szerint a rendszeres kabitoszer-fogyaszto havi <br>drogszuksegletenek ara szolid becslesek szerint is elerheti akar a 200 <br>ezer forintot. Torvenyszeru tehat, hogy a tobbmilliardos uzletet az <br>alvilag nem hagyja ki. Hazankban 1990-ben meg csak 6667 kg <br>kabitoszert foglaltak le, mig 1995-ben 681636 kilot. (MH) [Vagyis fel <br>evtized alatt SZAZSZOROSARA UGROTT A KABITOSZERKOBOZAS]<br><br>[Korrupt parlamenti kepviselok vannak a Zemplenyi botranyban]<br><br>A rendorseg a Zemplenyi-ugyben tanukent hallgatta ki a napokban <br>Jakone Szalma Borbalat, a Magyar Uszo Szovetseg egykori ugyvezeto <br>igazgatojat. A gazdasagi vezeto a televizio vasarnapi A Het cimu <br>musoraban kijelentette: tobb neves sportvezeto es parlamenti <br>kepviselo kozremukodese tette lehetove Zemplenyinek tobbmillio <br>forint kezhezvetelet, illetve utazgatasait. Jakone azota tobb nevtelen <br>fenyegetest kapott. Az MH ugy tudja, egyelore nem bukkantak olyan <br>jogtalan kifizetesre, amely alapjan meg lehetne allapitani barmelyik <br>neves sportvezeto, illetve sportdiplomata buntetojogi felelosseget. A <br>lap ertesulesei szerint Zemplenyi jelenleg korhazi kezelesre szorul, <br>ezert kihallgatasa szunetel.(MH)<br><br>==<br><br>Pokoli szektak <br>[Magyar Hirlap, aug. 5] <br>Szebeni Zsuzsa, Sengel Ferenc<br><br>Az elmult honapokban szamos modszeresen megkinzott, esetenkent <br>megeroszakolt (!) allattetemre talaltak orszagszerte. Majusban <br>peldaul tiz megnyuzott macskara bukkantak Kobanya egyik lakatlan <br>hazaban. Szakertok szerint a legtobb ilyen jellegu, brutalis <br>cselekmeny satanista szektak szamlajara irhato. Allatok <br>megeroszakolasara, szettepesere, esetleg felgyujtasara evente tobb <br>szaz pelda akad - veli Szabo Istvan Gyorgy vallasfilozofus, aki tizenot <br>eve foglalkozik az orszagban felbukkano extravagans vallasi <br>csoportok felterkepezesevel. Szerinte 1989 ota, a mintegy szaz <br>bejegyzett felekezeten kivul nehany veszelyes kozosseg is megjelent, <br>s az o szamlajukra irhato a legtobb ilyen hatborzongato cselekmeny. <br>A satanistak, a feketemagia vagy a feketemise hiveinek szama 18-20 <br>ezerre rug. S mind ujabb telepulesekrol es oktatasi intezmenyekbol <br>erkeznek jelzesek a ritualis eroszak terjedeserol. Allatvedelmi <br>torveny hijan a hatosagok eszkozei akkor is korlatozottak, ha esetleg <br>bizonyithato a kinzas.<br><br>Jo uzlet a forditott kereszt<br><br>A tizenevesek altal "sportbol" megkinzott macskak es kutyak esetei <br>mellett elsosorban a satanista csoportok "hasznalnak" <br>szertartasaikhoz kobor vagy lopott allatokat. Szakertok hazankban <br>20-25 olyan kisebb-nagyobb satanista tarsasag letezeserol tudnak, <br>amelyek egymastol fuggetlenul mukodnek. Jelkepeik - a forditott <br>kereszt, a 666-os szam, az ordogcsillag - forgalmazasa jo uzlet, igy <br>erre boltok es metalzenekarok egesz sora szakosodott. A kultusz <br>periferiajan megjeleno tinedzserek tulnyomo resze termeszetesen <br>csupan divatbol olti magara a szimbolumokat. A "hivoknek" azonban <br>- akik nehany kiveteltol eltekintve a 18-25 eves korosztalybol <br>kerulnek ki - mindennapjaik szerves reszeve valik a "gonosz erok" <br>tisztelete. <br><br>A tarsasagokon belul hierarchia nincs, kituntetett szerepe csak az <br>alapitonak van. <br><br>Lopni, sirokat es templomokat gyalazni, halottakkal fajtalankodni <br>vagy az eroszakot a szexualitassal kombinalni kifejezetten "jo" <br>cselekedetnek szamit. A kozosseg zart, kilepni nem lehet, aki esetleg <br>megprobalja, az folyamatos zaklatasnak teszi ki magat es csaladjat. <br>Nem ritka, hogy ilyen esetben a szulok nem birjak tovabb a <br>pszichikai, esetleg fizikai eroszakot es egyszeruen elkoltoznek az <br>adott telepulesrol. Szabo Istvan Gyorgy ugy veli, hogy vizsgalatai <br>egyertelmuen bizonyitjak: a satanista csoportok veszelyesseget nem <br>szabad lebecsulni. A csatlakozok tobbsege ugyanis nem divatbol vesz <br>reszt egy-egy kozosseg eleteben, hanem meggyozodesbol. Ez ugyan <br>hihetetlenul hangzik, azonban az eroszakos cselekmenyek utan <br>megszolaltatott fiatalokrol ez a hozzaertok egybehangzo velemenye - <br>fuzte hozza Szabo. A satanista ontudatosan vallalja "hitet", buszken <br>mesel a beavatasi szertartason elviselt fajdalomrol. Ugyanigy <br>elvezettel ecseteli sajat brutalitasat. Szabo, akit a rendorseg tobbszor <br>kert fel szakertonek olyan buncselekmenyek kapcsan, amikor az <br>elkoveto satanistanak vallotta magat, nem rejti veka ala, hogy az <br>elmult evekben legalabb 30-40 ongyilkossag, gyilkossag vagy sulyos <br>testi sertes oka a satankultusz. A jelenseg altal leginkabb fertozott <br>varosok - Budapest, Miskolc, Ozd es Debrecen - lakatlan epuleteiben, <br>nagyobb parkjaiban pedig rendszeresek a ritualis szertartasok. A <br>fovarosban kulonosen kedvelt talalkahely a Taban, a Margitsziget, a <br>Nepliget, valamint Obuda es Kobanya elhagyatottabb reszei.<br><br>A tragedia elkerulheto?<br><br>Szabo szerint elszomorito, hogy itthon mindossze nehany kutato <br>foglalkozik az extravagans vallasi csoportokkal. A nyugati <br>orszagokban regota felismertek: a leginkabb veszelyeztetett <br>korosztalyoknak mar az iskolaban lehetoseget kell adni, hogy <br>felkeszult szakemberektol kapjanak objektiv kepet a szelsoseges <br>szektakrol. Angliaban vagy Franciaorszagban intezmenyi hatter es <br>tucatnyi kiadvany segiti a pedagogusok, valamint a szocialis <br>munkasok tevekenyseget. Nalunk is ehhez hasonlo informacios bazis <br>felallitasara lenne szukseg - hangsulyozza. A Szaboval dolgozo <br>szociologusok, valamint neprajzosok munkajuk eredmenyet <br>egyebkent folyamatosan fejezetekbe rendszerezik. A tematikus <br>feldolgozas szempontjai: a kereszteny kozossegek, a keleti <br>vallasossag, a zsido felekezet (antiszemitizmus, neonaci mozgalmak), <br>a satanizmus, az afrikai gyokeru - az indian (eszak-del) eredetu, <br>valamint a kemiai vallasossag. Mint mondja, termeszetesen egyetlen <br>kozosseg eletebe sem akarnak beavatkozni, esetleg minositeni vallasi <br>eletuket. A hosszu tavu cel az, hogy a tanarok es a nevelesi <br>tanacsadok szakemberei felkeszultek legyenek, ha felbukkan egy-<br>egy ismeretlen vallasi kozosseg a kornyezetukben. A tragediak <br>tobbseget ugyanis hozzaerto szakemberekkel meg lehetne elozni. <br>Jelenleg azonban a helyzet nem valami biztato, hiszen kepzesre vagy <br>ismeretterjeszto kiadvanyok megjelentetesere nincs se penz, se <br>intezmenyi lehetoseg.  <br><br>==<br><br>LEVEL-VITA<br><br>Erdekes ez a Nemzet! Mondjuk ha rajtam mulna, azert rendet vagnek <br>az osszes "szentegyhaz"-ban, de azert ez a hitgyulekezet nevu <br>szemetdomb kulonosen kirivo! Csak az a baj, hogy a tarsadalmi es <br>gazdasagi melypont miatt el es virul ez a banda. A multkor <br>hallgattam egy kantorukat Pesten a Keleti-pu-nal, ha nagyon hulye <br>lennek, lehet, hogy en is bevennem azt a maszlagot (jelenlegi <br>katolikus egyhaz = balvanyimadas, ...), de igy sajna maximum a <br>fejenkenti egy golyot tudnam kiutalni nekik, nem az egy gomboc <br>fagyit.  [noname]<br><br>==<br><br>NYUGAT RUHELLI SZLOVAKIAT<br>[The Wall Street Journal August 5, 1996]<br> <br>Editorial  Slovakia: Left and Left Out <br> <br>Germany's Chancellor Helmut Kohl has refused for the last two years <br>to receive Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar in Bonn. Despite <br>Bratislava's angling for invitations, Paris and London haven't rolled <br>out the red carpet either. <br> <br>On recent a state visit to Austria, Mr. Kohl said he still wanted <br>Slovakia to join the European Union as soon as possible, "but at the <br>moment the preconditions have not improved, but rather gotten <br>worse." The Kohl admonition--the German chancellor is otherwise <br>relentlessly campaigning for the inclusion of Central Europe in the <br>EU--is only the latest of a series of warnings to Mr. Meciar. EU <br>foreign affairs commissioner Hans van den Broek has repeatedly <br>rebuked Bratislava for its abuses of democratic processes. The <br>Clinton administration's United Nations envoy Madeleine Albright, <br>and NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana have weighed in as well. <br> <br>As one of the carryovers from Czechoslovakia's Stalinist past, Mr. <br>Meciar made little effort to earn the West's trust and he has <br>squandered whatever remaining claim he had to Western <br>sympathies just in the last few months. Among other steps, he <br>tightened his party's authoritarian grip on the privatization agency, <br>the secret service and the media. His populist Movement for a <br>Democratic Slovakia seems bent on consolidating its power for a <br>1,000-year reich. <br> <br>In the neighborhood where Slovakia lives, next door to a thriving <br>Austria and Czech Republic, it would be rather hard to fail <br>economically. But despite a respectable macroeconomic record, <br>Slovakia cannot aspire to EU membership so long it remains under <br>the increasingly authoritarian control of Vladimir Meciar. EU <br>members, whatever their individual or collective shortcomings, know <br>that in the light of Europe's checkered history, it is important to <br>make genuine democracy a requirement for membership. <br> <br>Slovakia's President, Michal Kovac, is an ardent critic of his longtime <br>political rival, Mr. Meciar. "Continued political impasse in Slovakia <br>could have a negative impact on the Slovak economy and hinder the <br>country's entry in the EU and NATO," said Mr. Kovac at the recent <br>Central European summit of the World Economic Forum in Salzburg. <br>He was referring at that time to a conflict within Mr. Meciar's ruling <br>coalition, which was then on the brink of collapse. But the Meciar's <br>party's partnership with the Slovak National Party and the hardline <br>Communist Workers Union was rescued in a last-ditch effort. In a <br>joint effort that further harmed Slovakia's reputation, the red-brown <br>threesome nixed legislation to add opposition MPs to the secret <br>service control committee and postponed the planned overhaul of the <br>Fund for National Property, the body in charge of privatizations. <br>Presumably this was not the kind of solution to the impasse that Mr. <br>Kovac had in mind. <br> <br>EU officials were not amused either. "The participation of non-<br>governmental parties in the control of public life is a crucial point in <br>relations between Slovakia and the European Union," said Herbert <br>Bosch, the Austrian chairman of a joint committee of European and <br>Slovak MPs set up to prepare the ground for Slovakian EU <br>membership. <br> <br>But the deal was nothing new. Mr. Meciar has been working to <br>exclude opposition members from parliamentary institutions <br>overseeing the intelligence service and the privatization program <br>since he came to power. Television is entirely in the hands of Meciar <br>men; a few independent publications struggle for survival. <br> <br>Slovakia is no longer considered to be one of "Visegrad" countries, <br>even though it was part of Czechoslovakia when that country formed <br>the Visegrad alliance with Poland and Hungary after the Cold War's <br>end. Thus, it can not ride into the EU on the coattails of the Visegrad <br>nations, who are the prime candidates for membership. As long as <br>Mr. Meciar is in power, Slovakia will never become a EU member, <br>said the former Slovakian prime minister, Jan Carnogoursky, last <br>week in response to Helmut Kohl's negative remarks. And indeed, <br>there is no compelling reason for the EU to invite Slovakia in so long <br>as its government continues to misbehave. Vladimir Meciar and his <br>ardent Slovakian nationalism may yet prove to be an expensive <br>luxury for the people of his country.<br><br>==<br><br>BEALLT A MAGYAR GAZDASAGI VALSAG<br><br>[Igen jo emlekezetu olvasoink bizonyara emlekeznek arra, hogy a <br>"Suranyi-Bokros program" fo celja a magyar gazdasag <br>versenyhelyzetenek javitasa, azaz a gazdasag elenkitese volt a celja. <br>Nos, NAPRA PONTOSAN amikor a hazaarulo gazember Bokros <br>elnyerte "melto jutalmat" (zsiros Vilagbanki allast), a leghitelesebb <br>gazdasagi jelentesek szerint M.o. mar hivatalosan is "Gazdasagi <br>Valsag" allapotaba zullott! Ennyit a "Suranyi-Bokros"-fele NAGY <br>HAZUGSAGOKROL!]<br><br>Dow Jones Business News -- August 5, 1996 <br> <br>Hungary July Procurement Manager Index Falls To 48.5% <br>AP-Dow Jones News Service <br> <br>BUDAPEST -- The July Procurement Manager's Index fell to  48.5% <br>from 50.6% in June, the Hungarian Association of  Logistics, <br>Purchasing and Inventory Management (MLBKT) said  Monday. <br> <br>The drop indicates a move from recovery toward recession        <<<---<br>since the 50%-mark is the indicators' pivot, the MLBKT said. <br> <br>The PMI is the weighted average of five indicators. It  reflects <br>changes in production output, new orders, stocks  purchased, <br>delivery time and number of employees. <br><br> ==<br><br>LEVEL-VITA<br><br>Tisztelt Szerkeszto Ur!<br><br>A "Nemzet" magat magyarnak tartja ennek ellenere megis a magyar <br>sportolok  nevet rendszeresen idegen modon irja. Miert?  Talan oly <br>nehez visszairni angolbol magyar sorrendre? Kis dolgokban van az <br>ordog elbujtatva.<br><br>Tisztelettel:<br><br>Tamas Laszlo<br>From: "Laszlo Tamas (V)" <tamasl@pican.pi.csiro.au><br><br>-<br><br>Igy igaz, kis dolgokbol valoban sokat lehet megtudni. A "Nemzet", <br>ugy mint gyakorlatilag minden Internet-hirlap, sokban hagyatkozik <br>az Interneten fellelheto hirforrasokra. Tenyleg el lehet gondolkodni <br>azon, hogy a Nemzet kibocsatasa idopontjaig a sportszerkeszto NEM <br>TALALT MAGYAR OSSZESITEST sportoloink eredmenyeirol - mig a <br>szabad vilag (bar angolul, de) termeszetesen szamontartja a mi <br>eredmenyeinket is. Ugy latszik, az internacionalizmust lihego magyar <br>mediaszerkesztok talan "nacionalizmusnak" veltek volna sikereink <br>Interneten valo felsorolasat! <br><br>==<br><br>REGIONALIS HIREK<br><br>GROWING SUPPORT IN POLAND FOR EUROPEAN INTEGRATION. <br>According to a poll conducted from 24 to 29 May, 80% of Poles would <br>vote to join the EU, while 7% would vote against, compared to 72% for <br>and 9% against in 1995. The survey was taken by the Public Opinion <br>Research Center and published by Rzeczpospolita on 6 August. Only <br>6% believe in the immediate admission of Poland in the EU, 49% <br>believe it will take five years to gain admission. According to an <br>earlier EU-commissioned Eurobarometer survey, Poles and <br>Romanians were the keenest of all Central and Eastern Europeans to <br>join the EU. -- Jakub Karpinski<br><br>POLISH OPPOSITION PARTY ACCUSES KISZCZAK OF COMMITTING A <br>CRIME. The Movement for Poland's Reconstruction (ROP), led by <br>former Prime Minister Jan Olszewski, accused former Internal Affairs <br>Minister Gen. Czeslaw Kiszczak of committing a crime against the <br>interests of the Polish nation, Rzeczpospolita reported on 5 August. In <br>the 1980s Kiszczak -- one of the architects of martial law initiated in <br>1981 -- concluded agreements with the East German secret police <br>(Stasi), allowing it to conduct intelligence against Polish citizens and <br>institutions, Olszewski said. Olszewski said former Solidarity leaders, <br>including former President Lech Walesa, needed to answer whether <br>they concluded a secret agreement granting immunity to Kiszczak <br>and former Polish President Gen. Wojciech Jaruzelski in 1989. -- <br>Jakub Karpinski<br><br>CZECH-KYRGYZ "RADAR" DEAL IN PERIL. Although the sale was <br>approved more than 1 year ago, the Czechs have not delivered a <br>"Tamara" electronic detection system to Kyrgyzstan because the <br>Kyrgyz have not paid the $20 million it costs, CTK reported on 3 <br>August, citing the daily Mlada fronta Dnes. Supposedly able to detect <br>even stealth aircraft, Tamara is built by Tesla Pardubice, and the sale <br>was said to have saved the firm from bankruptcy. Often called a <br>radar system, Tamara in fact sends out no signals of its own. Instead, <br>it detects and analyses the electronic transmissions from its targets. <br>The report said experts believe the sale will not take place. -- Doug <br>Clarke<br><br>SLOVAK FOREIGN MINISTRY: HUNGARIAN EXPLANATION NOT GOOD <br>ENOUGH. Slovak Foreign Ministry representative Emil Kuchar said on <br>5 August that Hungary's explanation of its position on a declaration <br>calling for autonomy for Hungarians in neighboring countries "did not <br>fulfill Slovakia's expectations," TASR reported. Kuchar delivered the <br>ministry's opinion during a meeting with the Hungarian charge <br>d'affaires in Bratislava, Pal Benyo. The Hungarian declaration, issued <br>at a Budapest summit last month, caused concern in neighboring <br>countries as well as in the EU and U.S., the ministry said, adding that <br>Slovakia rejects the "institutionalization of ethnic differences," which <br>"disrupts the cultural mosaic of an open, civil society." Kuchar also <br>discussed the situation with representatives of the German, French, <br>and British embassies, while the ministry's State Secretary, Jozef <br>Sestak, met with U.S. Ambassador to Slovakia Ralph Johnson. In <br>Budapest, Slovak Ambassador to Hungary Eva Mitrova delivered <br>Slovakia's response to Hungary's Foreign Ministry. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>SLOVAK OPPOSITION PARTY PUBLICIZES PRIME MINISTER'S PLEDGE. <br>Pravda on 6 August published Vladimir Meciar's written pledge to <br>the Party of the Democratic Left (SDL), in which he guarantees a halt <br>to privatization until the National Property Fund (FNM) boards are <br>restructured to include opposition deputies. The pledge, dated 21 <br>June, was signed by Meciar during a coalition crisis. Although the <br>FNM boards will not be reconstructed until September at the earliest, <br>privatization continued on 1 August with the sale of 41 firms. SDL <br>deputy Lubomir Fogas said his party considers this step "an <br>expression of Meciar's political unreliability." FNM Presidium <br>President Stefan Gavornik said on 5 August that under pressure from <br>the ministers of agriculture, economy, and construction and public <br>works, preparations are being made for the privatization of other <br>firms, including banks, Praca reported. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>RFE/RL TO COMPLY WITH SLOVAK POLICE REQUEST. RFE/RL plans to <br>give police investigators a transcript of an interview with an <br>eyewitness of the kidnapping of President Michal Kovac's son, Sme <br>reported on 6 August. RFE/RL Director of Broadcasting Robert Gillette <br>told Sme that the station will provide it "as a gesture of goodwill <br>towards Slovak authorities and in the hope that the investigation will <br>be fully and justly resolved." Police investigator Jozef Ciz asked <br>RFE/RL for a copy in late July, after a prosecutor rejected his <br>adjournment of the investigation for lack of evidence. The interview <br>was broadcast by RFE/RL one week after the incident in late August <br>1995. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>HUNGARY'S SMALLHOLDERS PARTY REJECTS EXTREMIST LEADER'S <br>CALL FOR MERGER. Jozsef Torgyan, Chairman of the opposition <br>Independent Smallholder's Party (FKGP), on 5 August rejected Istvan <br>Csurka's proposal to merge with the opposition Christian Democrats <br>and Csurka's party, Hungarian media reported. Csurka, president of <br>the radical right-wing, non- parliamentary Hungarian Justice and <br>Life Party, suggested that the three parties' leaders resign "for the <br>benefit of a joint candidate for the post of prime minister" in the <br>1998 general elections. Torgyan said he is not willing to "smash apart <br>the FKGP as [was] done by the Nazis and the communists," and that <br>his mandate is to make his party the biggest in Hungary, one that <br>will "defeat liberalism and communism." Further, he rejected <br>Csurka's recent call for "civil disobedience." Torgyan's populist <br>rhetoric brought his party to the top of popularity polls in Hungary <br>last fall. -- Zsofia Szilagyi<br><br>EX-HUNGARIAN FINANCE MINISTER TO JOIN WORLD BANK. Former <br>Finance Minister Lajos Bokros has been named a senior consultant <br>with the World Bank, Hungarian media reported on 3 August. A <br>statement released by bank Vice President Jean Francois Richard <br>said Bokros will work in the institute's development department and <br>focus on capital movements, bank reform and privatization. Bokros <br>resigned as Hungary's finance minister in February. -- Zsofia Szilagyi<br><br>IFOR FINDS BIG SERB ARMS CACHE. Italian NATO troops accidentally <br>came upon a major Bosnian Serb arms depot while looking for <br>potential polling sites in Markovici, northeast of Sarajevo. The cache <br>had not been registered with IFOR and contains 1,000 tons of <br>weapons and ammunition occupying a space of 1,200 square meters, <br>AFP reported on 5 August. At least 4,000 Serbian civilians mobbed <br>the 30 Italians as they tried to begin carting off the ammunition, a <br>job that IFOR said would require 100 trucks to complete. Two <br>Bosnian Serb officers claimed that the site was about to be registered <br>with NATO, but the Italians noted that it had not been declared <br>before and was dangerously concealed near civilian housing. The <br>crowd in any event forced the Italians to return to the depot with <br>their trucks, the BBC noted. Under they Dayton agreement such <br>unauthorized caches can be confiscated and destroyed. -- Patrick <br>Moore<br><br><br>SUPREME COURT JUDGE: ILIESCU'S CANDIDACY UNCONSTITUTIONAL. <br>In an interview with the daily Romania libera, Judge Paul Florea of <br>the Romanian Supreme Court said incumbent president Ion Iliescu's <br>candidacy for a new term is unconstitutional, Reuters reported on 5 <br>August. The constitution stipulates that a president's mandate is <br>limited to a maximum of two consecutive terms. Romania libera had <br>earlier reported that Iliescu's campaign team had consulted the <br>constitutional court and had been unofficially advised that the <br>provision concerning a second term does not apply retroactively to <br>the adoption of the basic law. Iliescu had served as president of the <br>transitional legislative- executive body set up in December 1989, and <br>was elected president in May 1990. He was again elected in 1992, <br>after the passing of the country's new constitution, and his <br>supporters claim his renewed candidacy is for a constitutional second <br>term. -- Michael Shafir<br><br>ILIESCU STILL LEADING POLLS. According to a recent opinion poll, <br>the main opposition alliance, the Democratic Convention of Romania <br>(CDR), is the most popular "party" in parliamentary elections <br>scheduled for early November (33.5%), but President Ion Iliescu is <br>ahead (37.1%) in the presidential race that will be held at the same <br>time, the daily Libertatea reported on 6 August. The survey was <br>conducted by the Institute for Market and Social Analysis. CDR <br>candidate Emil Constantinescu trails Iliescu (31.6%), followed by the <br>candidate of the Democratic Party, Petre Roman (18.7%). In the <br>parliamentary race, the major ruling party, the Party of Social <br>Democracy in Romania, is backed by 27.5% of those polled. More than <br>a quarter of those questioned (26%) said either that they will not <br>vote or that they are undecided. -- Michael Shafir<br><br>BULGARIAN PRESIDENT ON POLITICAL SITUATION. President Zhelyu <br>Zhelev, in an interview with Trud on 5 August, repeated his position <br>that a presidential republic could help pull Bulgaria out of its present <br>crisis. Zhelev said the present parliamentary system has shown that <br>"it either works badly, or not at all." Zhelev called accusations that he <br>wants more power "not serious." He repeated that he will not run in <br>the upcoming elections but stay in politics after leaving the <br>presidency in January 1997. Also on 5 August, Zhelev met with the <br>united opposition's presidential candidate, Petar Stoyanov. Stoyanov <br>told RFE/RL that he and Zhelev agreed that the main problem in <br>Bulgaria is the government's mismanagement. Stoyanov said the <br>opposition supports Zhelev's foreign policy orientation. -- Stefan <br>Krause<br><br>CHECHENS LAUNCH MAJOR ASSAULT ON GROZNY. During the early <br>morning of 6 August, up to 300 Chechen militants attacked Grozny, <br>and heavy fighting was reported in several parts of the city, Western <br>and Russian agencies reported. Simultaneous attacks were launched <br>on the towns of Argun and Gudermes, east of the capital. Speaking at <br>a public rally in Grozny on 5 August, pro-Moscow head of state Doku <br>Zavgaev expressed his readiness to include in the new Chechen <br>government any members of the armed opposition who are prepared <br>to surrender their weapons, AFP reported. NTV reported on 5 August <br>that Chechen Chief of Staff Aslan Maskhadov had laid down new <br>conditions for a resumption of peace talks and is demanding that <br>Russian forces withdraw to the positions they occupied at the time of <br>the signing of the 10 June Nazran agreements and release all civilians <br>forcibly detained since that date. -- Liz Fuller<br><br>EXPLOSION ON PRIME MINISTER'S ROUTE. An explosion occurred on 6 <br>August on a Moscow highway only minutes before Prime Minister <br>Viktor Chernomyrdin was about to drive by on his way to work, <br>Russian and Western agencies reported. A police spokesman said it <br>was too early to say whether the blast was directed against <br>Chernomyrdin. Two days earlier, a hand grenade was found on a <br>train at the VDNKh metro station in northern Moscow, and on 3 <br>August a gunman held up a passenger train en route from Moscow to <br>Mariupol for 30 minutes before being arrested. -- Penny Morvant<br><br>YELTSIN RETURNS TO WORK. President Boris Yeltsin returned to work <br>at the Kremlin 5 August after spending three weeks at the Barvikha <br>sanitarium, ITAR-TASS reported. Yeltsin has decided to take his oath <br>of office on a specially prepared copy of the constitution adopted at <br>his insistence in a 1993 referendum. Presidential Chief of Staff <br>Anatolii Chubais has already rejected the idea of performing an ode <br>to the president at the inauguration, figuring it would be too <br>bombastic given the poor state of the Russian economy. The <br>ceremony is expected to last about an hour and Yeltsin's speech only <br>10 minutes due to his poor health, The New York Times reported. His <br>first inauguration took place as part of a session of the RSFSR <br>Congress of People's Deputies. -- Robert Orttung<br><br>ZYUGANOV STRESSES MODERATION, ACCUSES GOVERNMENT OF <br>PLAYING "GAME." Communist Party (KPRF) leader Gennadii Zyuganov <br>told ITAR-TASS on 5 August that his party has firmly rejected <br>"radical methods of struggle" and that unity among all left-wing <br>movements would only be possible when "those who have remained <br>in the last century" recognize that the new political environment <br>requires new methods of battle. On the same day, he accused the <br>government of deliberately withholding money owed to striking coal <br>miners in order to exacerbate tension in society, NTV and Russian TV <br>(RTR) reported. The ultimate purpose of the government's "game," <br>according to Zyuganov, is "the further collapse of the Russian <br>Federation." Zyuganov has consistently said that Communists and <br>their left-wing allies in parliament will decide whether to confirm <br>Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin only after the government <br>reveals its economic program. -- Laura Belin<br><br>COLONEL KILLED IN VORONEZH; ANOTHER ASSASSINATION ATTEMPT <br>FAILS. A Russian army colonel was killed on 5 August in his <br>apartment building in Volgograd, ORT reported. Colonel Yurii Kim, <br>rear services deputy commander of the 20th Motor Rifle Division of <br>the 8th Guard Corps, was killed by a bomb which exploded when he <br>stepped into the elevator. Kim was reportedly involved in business <br>activities. He served in Chechnya with current Duma Defense <br>Committee Chairman Lev Rokhlin, who caused a stir recently by <br>accusing senior Defense Ministry officers of corruption. Some press <br>reports have accused Rokhlin of involvement in dubious financial <br>transactions when he was based in Volgograd. Also on 5 August, an <br>unidentified attacker fired eight shots at the general director of the <br>Nizhnevartovskneft oil company, Khakim Gumerskii, Delovoi vtornik <br>reported on 6 August. Gumerskii was seriously injured. -- Penny <br>Morvant<br><br><br>ORT MANAGEMENT CRITICIZED. The 51% state-owned Channel 1 <br>broadcaster Russian Public TV (ORT) should not call itself "public," <br>since it only serves a narrow group of financial and political <br>interests, according to Izvestiya on 6 August. The paper said Boris <br>Berezovskii, deputy chairman of the ORT board of directors, wields <br>enormous power over programming decisions. Berezovskii owns <br>about 16% of the shares in ORT (other private investors own between <br>3% and 5%), and he helped finance the presidential campaigns of <br>both Boris Yeltsin and Aleksandr Lebed. The titular chairman of the <br>ORT board, Aleksandr Yakovlev, "has nothing to do with" running the <br>network. In fact, the paper said, ORT's board of directors is <br>"fictitious," as is its board of trustees. According to Izvestiya, other <br>figures who play an active role in ORT include presidential Chief of <br>Staff Anatolii Chubais and Deputy Prime Minister Vitalii Ignatenko, <br>who also heads the state-run ITAR-TASS news agency. -- Laura Belin<br><br>RUSSIA PROTESTS TURKEY'S REFUSAL TO ADMIT ZHIRINOVSKY. The <br>Russian Foreign Ministry called in the Turkish charge d'affaires in <br>Moscow and expressed "bewilderment" with Ankara's recent decision <br>to deny ultranationalist Vladimir Zhirinovsky an entry visa, Russian <br>media reported. Zhirinovsky had planned to vacation in a Turkish <br>coastal resort, but he was not allowed to board a plane in Moscow on <br>1 August because he did not have a visa. Zhirinovsky, trained as a <br>specialist in Turkish affairs, was expelled from Turkey in 1970 on <br>charges of distributing communist propaganda. He had been working <br>there as a translator. -- Scott Parrish<br><br>MOSCOW CITY TAKES OVER ZIL AUTO PLANT. The Moscow City <br>government will take over majority ownership of the city's ailing <br>auto giant, ITAR-TASS reported on 5 August. The city will buy 30% <br>of ZIL stock from the holding company Mikrodin to add to the 25% it <br>already owns. ZIL is running at a loss and was on the verge of firing <br>several thousand workers. Last year, it produced 10,000 vehicles, <br>half of its output in 1994. -- Peter Rutland<br><br>ECONOMIC SLUMP CONTINUES. The economy continued to decline in <br>the first half of this year, according to official statistics reported by <br>Finansovye izvestiya on 6 August. GDP dropped by 5% over the same <br>period in 1995, while industrial output fell 4%, agricultural <br>production fell 7%, and the volume of investment plunged by 14%. <br>Although the monthly rate of inflation dropped to 0.7% in July, the <br>situation in the financial sphere is deteriorating. The budget deficit <br>as a proportion of revenue went up from 22% in January-June 1995 <br>to 47% this year, and wage arrears reached 29.8 trillion rubles ($5.7 <br>billion at the current exchange rate) in July. The proportion of loss-<br>making industrial enterprises increased from 26% of the total in <br>January-May 1995 to 36% during the same period this year. -- <br>Natalia Gurushina<br><br>This material was reprinted with permission of the Open Media     <br>Research Institute, a nonprofit organization with research offices in     <br>Prague, Czech Republic. For more information on OMRI publications,     <br>please write to:  info@omri.cz  <br>
